Are you ready for some exciting news? @kohenmeyers will be opening his booking for summer 2023 on April 7th for just 48 hours! This is your chance to submit your tattoo project for consideration. While larger projects will take priority, he is also open to single session ideas. Be sure to mark your calendars and don't miss out on this opportunity. Keep in mind that due to high demand, not all submissions will be selected, but he will carefully choose the ones that best align with his body of work at the moment.

The 40 minute outline… did ya catch that? My cinematography skills of panning to the clock? I was going to edit the sound, but I think that the chaos of it actually worked out perfect. Especially the more quite part while putting the stencil on, you couldn’t really plan it better. This was the first one you will have to stay tuned for the next video! Tyler has his second appointment in about a month. Thanks @kohenmeyers @cashmanelaflare for letting me document this in order to stay up to date on all things social media.

Welcome Tattoo is hiring! We are looking for a customer service-oriented individual to fill a Counter person position. As our Counter Person, you will be responsible for a range of tasks, including cleaning, multitasking, answering phones, scheduling appointments, greeting customers, and more.

The ideal candidate will be outgoing and enjoy interacting with people. Excellent communication skills and attention to detail are a must, along with the ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment. Prior experience in customer service is a plus.

Please note that this position does not lead to an apprenticeship, and applicants looking to tattoo need not apply.

This is a part-time position, and weekend availability on Saturday and Sunday is required. There is room for growth within the position. 

If you're interested in joining our team, please click on the link in our bio to apply. We look forward to hearing from you!

NOW HIRING! We are currently searching for the right tattooer to join our team. The ideal person will have several years of tattooing experience and a strong desire to grow as an artist. If you are an artist with expertise in black and gray tattoos, fine line work, and floral designs that would be a plus. If you are passionate about your art, dedicated to providing great customer service, and possess the necessary skills, you might just be the person we are searching for.

Working at Welcome you have the option for the counter to take care of scheduling appointments, managing client inquiries, and ensuring a smooth flow of bookings. 

If you're interested in joining us, please reach out via email. Please note that, at this time, we do not offer any apprenticeship positions. We look forward to hearing from you and discussing potential opportunities.

📣Announcement📣 We're excited to announce Abby @newcompbook will be joining us at Welcome Tattoo! She will start on December 1st and has flash available and will be taking on new projects. Abby, a Micronesian-American tattoo artist, began her tattooing journey in early 2022 after a lifelong love for art and tattoos. Hailing from North Carolina, she honed her craft within the diverse queer tattooing scene of Los Angeles, specializing in fineline and illustrative black and grey, while remaining open to diverse styles. As an artist, Abby prioritizes creating a safe and comfortable environment that brings joy to people from all walks of life. In her free time, she enjoys the outdoors, weightlifting, crafting, and exploring new music. If you're interested in her work, contact the shop directly to set up a consultation!
